  {
    q: "I changed the remote batteries and it still doesn't work.",
    a: "There are two batteries in most modern gas fireplace remote systems, not one. The handheld transmitter has its own batteries (usually AA or AAA), and the receiver module inside the firebox housing has its own batteries (usually 4 AA, sometimes a 9V). Most owners replace the handheld batteries and stop there. The receiver batteries can drain in 1-2 years on Skytech and IntelliFire systems. We pull the receiver during the diagnostic and check both. About 30% of remote calls end here at the diagnostic with a battery swap, no parts, $120 total.",
