    q: "What's an IPI module?",
    a: "IPI stands for Intermittent Pilot Ignition. It's the electronic ignition system that fires the pilot only when you call for heat (rather than running a standing pilot continuously). IPI modules cycle a spark electrode against a ground rod to light the pilot, sense the pilot via the same electrode (flame rectification), then open the main valve when proven. Common in Heat & Glo IntelliFire, Mendota, and most 2010+ direct-vent installs. When the IPI module fails, the system won't light at all on remote command. Year 8-12 typical replacement window. $340-540 typical fix.",
